 Petroview� Product Spec Analyse information more effectively with PetroView 
The Petroview� supplied by Deloitte & Touche Llp are used in the subsea oil and gas industry. PetroView is a Geographic Information System (GIS), which allows spatial analysis of the upstream oil and gas industry..


Petroview� 
 Specification and Data: 


Pressure Rating: 
 


Temperature Rating:  
 


Water Depth Rating: 
 


Category:  
 







Petroview� by Deloitte & Touche Llp, PetroView is a Geographic Information System (GIS), which allows spatial analysis of the upstream oil and gas industry. 
PetroView is an essential tool for exploration, new ventures and business planning. The output of analysis can be easily incorporated into reports and presentations.
The system is fast and easy to use, carrying detailed information on:
exploration, appraisal and development wells; 
licence areas and partner interests; 
field developments; and 
infrastructure. 
This wealth of information combined with cultural data, creates comprehensive and accurate datasets that can be viewed and analysed in map, graph or report format.
PetroView may also be customised, enabling users to easily import and visualise their own corporate data, such as, seismic navigation inventories, structural geology layers, production records, or any other spatial data. Additionally, a range of modular add-ons have been created to support field analysis, well trading, historic licence and deals analysis and prospect data management. 
Since the launch of PetroView in 1992, we have continuously enhanced the tool to embrace the latest technology, whilst retaining a user-friendly interface. PetroView is now available as a desktop and web-based solution. Many oil and gas companies, contractors and financial institutions regard PetroView as the most comprehensive data visualisation package available for the upstream oil and gas industry.
..find out more about this product at Deloitte & Touche Llp



